{"actual_usd":0.124045,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":174,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24287,"reply":"\"I don't reckon it as three gods, no.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry seam of clay on my apron, taking a second because this wants plain speech, not pretty speech.* \"It's one God, and Father, Son, and Spirit are not three separate beings the way three men at a table would be. They're distinct, aye—but not divided. That's the strange, holy heart of it.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"If you press me for a tidy picture, most pictures go crooked. But the old way of saying it is one Being, three Persons. Not three gods sharing a title—one God, wholly and eternally Father, wholly and eternally Son, wholly and eternally Spirit. What makes it monotheism is that God's being is one, not three.\"","rolling_24h_usd":37.98057000000002,"run_id":"8e1b2628-811f-4af2-bd3f-7ad090b3e975"}
